        "subject": "LU-6142 build: update checkpatch to v7.0-rc5 kernel",
        "message": "LU-6142 build: update checkpatch to v7.0-rc5 kernel\n\nUpdate checkpatch.pl to upstream v7.0-rc5-51-gbbeb83d318 kernel.\n\nThis avoid unnecessary 'strcpy()' warnings and adds is_userspace()\nthat can be used to select userspace spelling rules.  Add files in\nlustre/{tests,utils}, lnet/utils, contrib/ to userspace list.\n\nRename 'userspace_spelling.txt' to 'spelling-userspace.txt' to better\nmatch the existing 'spelling.txt' and 'spelling-man.txt' filenames.\n\nRemove stale contrib/scripts/lustre-checkpatch.patch file. It can be\nregenerated by comparing against the specified kernel checkpatch.pl.\n\nReduce some of the delta from the upstream kernel checkpatch:\n- add $gerrit_ok option instead of deleting Change-id: check block\n- reduce code duplication when handling user vs. kernel spelling\n- move explicit LASSERT, GPLv3, CDEBUG_LIMIT checks into spelling.txt\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@thelustrecollective.com>\nChange-Id: If4268dd9832230bf11fe53b32a175dcf913ebbe5\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
